## Unit 3: Lesson 34 - Arrays and Loops: Hidden Images

# Background

Arrays and loops can be used to uncover hidden images. To reconstruct the original image, use loops to access individual pixels of an image and the relative position of indices.

# Lesson

* Design an program to reveal a hidden image.
* Design an program to scramble an image or create a visual effect. 


